<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98597106372945></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98597106372945><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=98597106372945>RE: Good Weapon?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=98597106372945#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17100><span id=Sage>sleepybri</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>38 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 30th 11:51 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.85]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You can either do one of two things, either spend what you got to get something new, or save up for a weapon that will stay with you for some time.&nbsp;&nbsp;I don't know how much money you've been able to save, but I'll try to give some advice anyways.<br>The Axe of the Iron Back (16dmg/37delay) is a great weapon for your lvl and goes for around 70pp or less.  My first purchase was the Blackened Iron Bastard Sword (20/47) which can be had for around 200pp, then I was able to move up to a Slivery Two-Handed Axe which was an amazing weapon(21/48).  But as a ShadowKinght I would recommend starting to save up for a Dark Reaver, they're great weapons and there prices have been falling greatly recently, you should be able to pick one up for around 300pp.  If ya need anymore info, let me know.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
