<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98629840750025></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98629840750025><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=98629840750025>RE: Good Weapon?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=98629840750025#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>112 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 3rd 7:46 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.85]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First I'd say you need to get a magic weapon, or any sort.&nbsp;&nbsp;My recommendation would be to get a velium longsword or a frozen longsword, either should run about 5-10pp and allows you to hit those anoying creatures that require magic weapons.  I'd then recommend the Axe of the Iron Back for about 50pp now, or if you have 300pp buy the Runic Carver/Dark Reaver (the Dark Reaver being better in the long run).  <br>   Other choices for weapons on a budget would be: Tower Guard Blade 2hs (100pp) fast but low damage, 2h Practise Sword (150pp) higher damage but really slow, Sap of Piety 1hb 13/36 more expensive but a very nice weapon (300pp), Sarnak Enforcer 1hb (100pp or less).  And definately get a good piercer, recommend either a bloodstained fang or Walrus Tooth (tooth is better), there are some really nice piercing weapons for the mid game now.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
